value: Siberia, Manchuria and Korea; winters to s China and n India

Breeds Amur and lower Ussuri River region of Siberia and Manchuria; Korea; formerly Japan. Winters south to Fukien, China, occasionally Taiwan, southern Ryukyu Islands; has wandered north to southern Yakutia, south to eastern India.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: on breeding grounds requires tall trees or man-made structures for nesting & wetlands or agricultural land for feeding;winters in wetland habitats:estuarine & freshwater wetalnds, paddyfields, marshes etc
